<li>Write the full form and one-line use of: HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, SMTP.</li>
Answer:- Term            Full Form                                Uses
        1.HTTP          HyperText Transfer Protocol             Used to transfer web pages and data between a web browser and a web server.
        2.HTTPS         HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure      Used to securely transfer web pages and data by encrypting communication between the browser and server.
        3.FTP           File Transfer Protocol                  Used to upload and download files between a computer and a server over a network.
        4.SMTP          Simple Mail Transfer Protocol           Used to send emails from an email client to a mail server or between mail servers.
        
<li>What is the difference between IPv4 and IPv6? Answer in 2 lines.</li>
Answer:- IPv4 uses 32-bit addresses (e.g., 192.168.1.1) and supports about 4.3 billion unique IP addresses,
         which are now becoming limited due to the growth of internet-connected devices.

        IPv6 uses 128-bit addresses (e.g., 2001:db8::1) and provides an almost unlimited number of unique IP addresses.
        It also offers better security, improved network performance, and more efficient routing than IPv4.
        
