<li>What do these HTTP status codes mean: 200, 301, 404, 500, 403?</li>
Answer:- HTTP Status code                   Meaning
         1.200 OK                         The request was successful, and the server returned the requested resource.
         2.301 Moved Permanently          The requested page has been permanently moved to a new URL, and the browser should use the new address.
         3.403 Forbidden                  The server understands the request but refuses access because the user does not have permission.
         4.404 Not Found                  The requested page or resource could not be found on the server.
         5.500 Internal Server Error      The server encountered an unexpected problem and could not complete the request.
         
<li>Explain DNS hierarchy (root, TLD, domain, subdomain) with www.google.com as an example.</li>
Answer:- The DNS (Domain Name System) hierarchy is a tree-like structure that helps convert a domain name (such as www.google.com) into 
          an IP address that computers can understand.
                Root (.)
                  |
                .com      ← Top-Level Domain (TLD)
                  |
              google      ← Domain Name
                  |
                 www       ← Subdomain (Host)
